{"type":"message","id":"cdceb2de","parentId":"a813fd14","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:11:12.205Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qtmmptxaqvoa_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 170102\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: a (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the ONE concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most immediate next action is:\r\n\r\n**TIC Experiment** - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThis is the \"NEXT ACTION\" from Phase 1 Advancement. The pending action is to:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that COMPRESSION and CAUSAL DISCOVERY are the SAME problem - causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSo I should:\r\n1. Create a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script/classifier\r\n2. It should analyze recent pulse logs\r\n3. Classify content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Try to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me look at the recent pulse logs to understand the format. The last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-23 165102.md`.\r\n\r\nI need to create a TIC classifier implementation. This could be a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Analyzes content for invariants (stable concepts across sessions) vs variants (novel/unique content)\r\n3. Attempts prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. A working TIC classifier would demonstrate that compression and causal discovery are the same problem, collapsing Phase 1 and Phase 2.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the initial TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns. This will be the foundation for measuring classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES_FOR_INVARIANT = 3  # Must appear in N sessions to be \"invariant\"\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.concept_frequency = Counter()\r\n        self.invariant_concepts = set()\r\n        self.variant_concepts = set()\r\n        \r\n    def extract_concepts(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract significant concepts from pulse text.\"\"\"\r\n        # Remove code blocks, paths, timestamps\r\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'```[\\s\\S]*?```', '', text)\r\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'`[^`]+`', '', cleaned)\r\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[\\d\\s:]*', '', cleaned)\r\n        cleaned = re.sub(r'[a-zA-Z]:\\\\[^\\s]+', '', cleaned)  # Windows paths\r\n        \r\n        # Extract capitalized multi-word phrases and key terms\r\n        concepts = []\r\n        phrases = re.findall(r'\\b[A-Z][a-z]+(?:\\s+[A-Z][a-z]+)+\\b', text)\r\n        concepts.extend(phrases)\r\n        \r\n        # Key technical terms\r\n        terms = re.findall(r'\\b(?:TIC|?|compression|invariance|causal|gap|decay|pulse|session|synthesis|architecture)\\b', \r\n                          text, re.IGNORECASE)\r\n        concepts.extend([t.lower() for t in terms])\r\n        \r\n        return concepts\r\n    \r\n    def learn_from_pulses(self, pulse_files: List[Path]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Learn invariant/variant patterns from pulse history.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_concepts = []\r\n        \r\n        for pf in sorted(pulse_files):\r\n            text = pf.read_text()\r\n            concepts = self.extract_concepts(text)\r\n            pulse_concepts.append(set(concepts))\r\n            self.concept_frequency.update(concepts)\r\n        \r\n        # Invariant = appears in >= MIN_PULSES_FOR_INVARIANT pulses\r\n        for concept, freq in self.concept_frequency.items():\r\n            if freq >= MIN_PULSES_FOR_INVARIANT:\r\n                self.invariant_concepts.add(concept)\r\n            else:\r\n                self.variant_concepts.add(concept)\r\n        \r\n        return {\r\n            'total_concepts': len(self.concept_frequency),\r\n            'invariants': len(self.invariant_concepts),\r\n            'variants': len(self.variant_concepts),\r\n            'invariant_ratio': len(self.invariant_concepts) / max(1, len(self.concept_frequency))\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def classify(self, text: str) -> Tuple[set, set]:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify concepts in text as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        concepts = self.extract_concepts(text)\r\n        invariants_found = set()\r\n        variants_found = set()\r\n        \r\n        for c in concepts:\r\n            if c.lower() in [i.lower() for i in self.invariant_concepts]:\r\n                invariants_found.add(c)\r\n            else:\r\n                variants_found.add(c)\r\n        \r\n        return invariants_found, variants_found\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, recent_pulses: List[str]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict likely invariants in next pulse based on recent history.\"\"\"\r\n        if not self.invariant_concepts:\r\n            return {'prediction': 'unknown', 'confidence': 0.0}\r\n        \r\n        # Higher confidence if recent pulses have high invariant overlap\r\n        recent_invariants = []\r\n        for pulse in recent_pulses[-5:]:\r\n            inv, _ =\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 17:01:26"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1307,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 170102\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: a (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the ONE concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most immediate next action is:\r\n\r\n**TIC Experiment** - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThis is the \"NEXT ACTION\" from Phase 1 Advancement. The pending action is to:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that COMPRESSION and CAUSAL DISCOVERY are the SAME problem - causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nSo I should:\r\n1. Create a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script/classifier\r\n2. It should analyze recent pulse logs\r\n3. Classify content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Try to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me look at the recent pulse logs to understand the format. The last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-23 165102.md`.\r\n\r\nI need to create a TIC classifier implementation. This could be a Python script or PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Analyzes content for invariants (stable concepts across sessions) vs variants (novel/unique content)\r\n3. Attempts prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to v